		<hr align="left" width="100%" />
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40215">I'm setting up a campaign, typical dnd3.5 setting, nothing to out of the ordinary.<br />
The problem I'm having is that one of the people in the campaign is dying to use a character that is simply to powerful.<br />
The character was created and run in another campaign with a DM that loved to hand out magic items like they're candy, and has a penchant for turning PCs into.. things.<br />
So, this character, which had been an atypical lawful good monk, somehow got cursed into being a vampire.<br />
I don't want to just simply flat out refuse to let him use the character, but I need to reign his character in greatly.<br />
He's got skills from monk/shadowdancer/vampire currently, if i recall correctly.<br />
Any suggestions would be appreciated... </div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
	<br>
