<div align="left">
		
		<hr align="left" width="100%" />
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40219">Reroll, unless you really want that character to be a part of the story. I hate cleaning up other GM's ubers when they want to come to game. With 2e, it's not a big problem, power = magic items + level. In 3.5e, you have feats and prestige classes that let people do all sorts of sick things.....but you can't take those from them like you can a simple +5 Sunblade of Blood-drinking-Defense. Good GMs can work power deprivation into the game, rust monsters, thieves, mysterious draining of magic, whatever, but you can't take feats and prestige abilities, it's like stealing xp from players. I guess if you really wanted to, knock him back a few levels, i.e. he loses the bonus feats, i.e. he misses the pre-reqs for certain feats and prestige classes, so he'll be less powerful.<br />
<br />
<br />
Having a PC vampire is the worst idea ever though. Nothing short of a total undead party ever makes that work. Have them re-roll, my best suggestion.  "They will come back, come back again, as long as the Red Earth rolls. He never wasted a tree or a leaf, why should he squander souls?"<br />
<br />
"The road to Hell is paved with good intentions</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
