<div align="left">
		
		<hr align="left" width="100%" />
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40222">Quote:heh and remember, vampirism = a magical affliction that turns you chaotic evil.<br />
<br />
Not always. I have seen a character play a lawful good vampire and do it WELL. Basically this characters history was RPed well enough to show that his indomitable will was enough to fight back the evil and choatic tendancies. Because of this our GM allowed him to skip the alignment change, although the fact that he was forced to drink blood did weigh on his consience constantly and he had to deal with it.<br />
<br />
It all depends on a number of factors.<br />
<br />
1) Is it his gear that makes him too powerful?<br />
<br />
If so, take some of it away. Even before the game begins. Whatever event brings this character to meet the rest of the party could strip him of his items. Be it a magical portal the moves only flesh, or if he was captured and the  group rescued his naked body with nothing else. There are many ways to separate a player from his stuff.<br />
<br />
2) Is it the vampirsm that makes him too powerful?<br />
<br />
Use it against him. Have them be attacked constantly during the day and have people hate him even if he tries to be 'good'. Have a local vampire hunter find out about him a decide to add him to his trophy list. These are things called 'story hooks'. I use them a lot to remind 'special' characters that they are special.<br />
<br />
3) Is it his level or EL that makes him too powerful?<br />
<br />
Here, the player has to know that the game is set for a specific level. Figure up his EL (vampire level + class levels) and let him know that he can only keep x number of levels.<br />
<br />
Hope this has been helpful. Personally I enjoy running high level / high power games myself, and I have learned that there are many 'tricks' to control powerful characters.<br />
<br />
Ask me sometime about my campaign that consisted of 4 34th level characters, each paragons of thier race, gifted with deific power. Now THAT was a power trip.<br />
<br />
EDIT: sig... <i>Edited by: Kanaellars at: 10/16/03 11:51 am<br />
</i></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
	<br>
<br>
