		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40226">I would think he problem is more about the 'Vampire' part of the issue.<br />
<br />
You could tell him that much of the campaign will take place during the day and a vampire would not fit.<br />
You could put a vampire hunter twice his level on his tail, he be making a new character soon because it seems like he's the type that dosn't know how to play a vamp-in-hiding.\<br />
Have a wandering cleric find him when he's sleeping and cast ressurection on him.  <br />
Maybe you could say your campaign world looses its connection with the negetive material plane for a short peroid of time, write it into the history of the world.  Or better yet, they 'tunnel' the brought him to this world cause its to be severed.  If he looses his connection to the plane he dies.  Then the place he arrives conviently is a temple where the clerics bring him back because they have a prophecy that he's supposed to be a great hero or something.  That same tunnel would turn all of his magic items mundane.  &quot;See this, its my quarterstaff of fireballs. Watch this 'Fireball!'&quot; &amp;lt;nothing happens&gt; &quot;Ya right 'Staff of fireballs'.  Thats a good one&quot; </div>
