<div align="left">
		
		<hr align="left" width="100%" />
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40228">first of all, being a Vampire carries a very high EL.  Adjust the other characters' level upwards, or adjust the vampire's level downwards, and explain to him why this is done - being a vampire = high EL, end of story.<br />
<br />
secondly, why do DMs hate character power?  I mean, isn't that the goal of the player - to amass power so that his character can't be killed by those who wish to do him harm?  Sure, once the player gets a +187 sword of own, he can walk all over all the NPCs you had ready to thwart him - because that's exactly what would happen if that PC got a powerful weapon anyway!  Just give the PCs more powerful enemies to fight, and make sure there's an in-game reason - great warriors from another realm or plane have heard about the power of overpwered_character01 and are coming to test his might.  Chances are, if one character's overpowered enough for the party to start fighting too difficult opponents, the rest of the party will start resenting this person!  Always try to get the players to do your work for you.  And if they stick together and manage to defeat the monsters despite your efforts - hooray players!  Because, again, isn't that what dungeons &amp;amp; dragons is all about?   -- Marauder Arafain Entreri, 65 Deceiver<br />
  -- Arafein Soulstriker, 54 Champion Relic (deceased)<br />
  -- Arafax Kokorozan, 20 Monk Giantfriend (missing)<br />
  -- Formerly of Requiem of Souls and Crusaders of Plilo<br />
  -- Formerly of The Rathe Server, now of Zebuxoruk<br />
  -- My ghetto gear<br />
&quot;Once, in the old west, a gentleman shot a professional gunfighter in the back. When asked why he didn't give the other chap a chance to draw, he replied, 'Well, he's dead and I'm alive and that's how I wanted it to be.&quot; -- from Red Planet, Robert A. Heinlein<br />
<br />
</div>
