		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40231">Quote:Forgive me, but that's not a consequence of his starting character level, it's a starting consequence of someone not caring about the game.<br />
<br />
Well, based on level alone, no. But levels, power, items, all of that, jumping into a game with all the big guns, players are more apt to take it less seriously, they haven't worked for it. <br />
<br />
Quote:Well, ideally, the world should punish your players for their actions, not you as the DM - if the players do something unconscionable, have the local justice system try to punish them for it - if the players stomp all over the posse sent to capture them, the magistrate can hire a hero from another town.<br />
<br />
Same difference in what I said. DMs have to decide to send the posse out. That's putting the smack down. That's the world putting the smack down. I see PCs like one branch of the criminal justice system sees crime, you're more likely to offend than play by the rules. I see players as more likely to use their abilities and powers recklessly than constructively.  </div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
