		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40232">Quote: I see PCs like one branch of the criminal justice system sees crimeIn other words, you don't have any respect for your players and you aren't running the game for their benefit, they're simply annoyances that get in your way and mess up your plans?<br />
<br />
I'm sorry, but that sounds like an attitude that is going to make for a frustrating game for everyone involved.  As a DM, I always try to cater to the players, and let them play the game they want - but my NPCs never pull punches and if the PCs run afoul of a big nasty, they get both barrels without hesitation.  PCs are much too resourceful to do otherwise, and fighting a relentless, implacable enemy is much more entertaining than &quot;killing monsters&quot;.   -- Marauder Arafain Entreri, 65 Deceiver<br />
  -- Arafein Soulstriker, 54 Champion Relic (deceased)<br />
  -- Arafax Kokorozan, 20 Monk Giantfriend (missing)<br />
