		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40233">Quote:In other words, you don't have any respect for your players and you aren't running the game for their benefit, they're simply annoyances that get in your way and mess up your plans?<br />
<br />
Slow down there cochees. I didn't say a single word of that. But I assume the worst in player behavior. Players deciding how to act in a situation is all part of the game. That doesn't mean some of their behavior isn't destructive to the game. If it's part of the story, they can damn well do what they please. If they are ruining the story, for everyone else, and for me, it's bad gaming. That's what I seek to avoid. And I prep to have my bases covered against PCs going over the top or running wild.  </div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
