		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40235">Bad gaming: Taking up a plot line, then sabotaging it, not because it's clever, not because it accomplishes anything, but simply because the player felt like it. If the whole party was on that track, then I'd let it go, let it develop. If it's one person spoiling what the rest of the party is working towards, it's destructive, especially if it happens repeatedly. And it happens to my group, repeatedly. </div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
