		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40238">Or just go in without a plotline.<br />
<br />
About the 3rd time my group decided not to follow a plotline that I had put a lot of work into I decided to stop putting so much work into fixed piece/module like adventures.  I put more effort into developing the political and social environment, quietly sinking hooks into the characters that way, and adventure followed.<br />
<br />
I still have a couple of my heavier plotline &quot;modules&quot; laying around.  The people of the petty kingdoms on the Great Eastern Sea are plagued by &quot;rogue mermen&quot; to this very day   </div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
