		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40240">I have the same DMing tatic.  I cant seem to get it to work right with any game except Shadowrun though.    Dont know what it is but I have people Rave over my Shadowrun campaigns.  My D&amp;amp;D campaigns always end up 'blah' by half way through.<br />
<br />
Dont get me wrong, I love the Shadowrun setting.  But theres only so many times that you can do a type of run before it gets old.  I really started mixing things up once and the campaign got massive. One player ended up as a mafia don, played it all out.  Then he ended up marrying his female bodyguard.  Since they still wanted to play I had quite a storyline going with her as well.  Not to mention their frequent encounters with the Yak.  And the smuggling ring that was going on in the background that they had a slight part of.  Plus his political connections that they had to keep up and going.  Their matrix buddies that were taking on the &amp;lt;Renraku&gt; Archology Rogue AI.  There just wasnt a good stopping point because there was so many storylines going on.  The campaign took up a life of its own, I never really had to setup any sort of adventure. Just had the NPC's react to what was going on.  Was really fun. </div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
