		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40242">Have a GM here that gets rather heavy handed with the 'table chat'.  (Some of you may remember him from a previous story, he's the guy that put us in the pit and didnt let us out)<br />
<br />
We were playing some StarWars the other day and the captian was on the comm with the imperial star destroyer.  (We were getting permisson to land on the planet, we were rebels going to retreive a downed pod and using &quot;visiting family&quot; as our cover.)  He tells the guy on the other end of the comm &quot;We have a passanger that is visiting reletives.&quot; then turns to the group and says &quot;That's what we were going to tell them right?&quot;<br />
GM takes it as his character saying that to us sitting there in the cockpit while he has an open channel.  So things get abit rough.<br />
Then later we were talking to an NPC asking him some questions.  We got all our questions answered and started to talk amongst ourselves in a farily &quot;Party Private&quot; conversation.  (Ya, lets just tell everyone that were here retreiving some sensitive rebellion information during an imperial occupation)  and the GM takes it that were standing in front of this guy talking.  More chaos ensues.<br />
<br />
Sometimes this guy runs games that are alright, but its nights like this that he turns out as a real 'pick GM'.  Ends up more of a stress generator than a fun time.  And theres not talking with him about it either.  &quot;What do you think im just going to give you everything?&quot;<br />
Im not talking about assuming a rogue is sneaking in a dangerous enviroment either.  Im talking about simple things.  Like assuming that table chatter is just that.  One of our players is known for babbling on about things unrelated to the game.  So were flying through hyperspace and the captian starts talking about something that happened to his SWG character.  As far as the GM's concerned his Star Wars character plays Star Wars Galaxies.   </div>
