		<hr align="left" width="100%" />
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_40243">Nenjin, I'm sorry, but I fail to see what connection there is between placing a limit on character power (which you've talked about in this thread and others) and players being selfish and impatient (which seemed to be the difficulties in all the examples you gave).  I'm forced to agree with Llabak - it sounds like your players simply don't want to cooperate.  I'm familiar with this and I've run into it plenty of times in my own gaming group - the answer is, DON'T TRY TO CATER YOUR CAMPAIGN TOWARDS YOUR PLAYERS.  Run the game world, and make it clear the progress of events is in their hands - if they end up arguing amongst themselves and a party-on-party war ensues, and they don't have a lot of fun with the campaign because of it, guess what - it's THEIR fault!  As long as you simply run the campaign and don't get involved, they can't blame you, and the game goes on.   -- Marauder Arafain Entreri, 65 Deceiver<br />
  -- Arafein Soulstriker, 54 Champion Relic (deceased)<br />
  -- Arafax Kokorozan, 20 Monk Giantfriend (missing)<br />
  -- Formerly of Requiem of Souls and Crusaders of Plilo<br />
  -- Formerly of The Rathe Server, now of Zebuxoruk<br />
